1. Download Mercurial

2. Download Python Dev
 sudo apt-get install python-dev

3. Download and Install RVM and ruby

3. Download Vim from Mercurial
 hg clone https://vim.googlecode.com/hg/ vim
 hg pull
 hg update

4.1 Install ruby-dev

4.2 Install Vim
 ./configure --prefix=/usr/local \
              --enable-gui=no \
              --without-x \
              --disable-nls \
              --enable-multibyte \
              --enable-pythoninterp \
              --enable-rubyinterp \
              --with-features=huge

6. Clone .dotfiles repo

7. Install Vundle
 git clone https://github.com/gmarik/vundle.git ~/.vim/bundle/vundle

8. Vim BundleInstall

9. http://deangerber.com/blog/2012/01/09/vim-caught-deadly-signal-segv/

10. Install Tmux
